Package: honestlm
Title: Guardrails for Teaching Linear Models
Version: 0.0.0.9007
Authors@R:
    person("Yaniv", "Brandvain", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "ybrandva@umn.edu")
Description: Provides small, opinionated wrappers around familiar linear model
    workflows. The package keeps base R and ggplot2 interfaces recognizable
    while adding guardrails around common interpretation traps, including
    coefficient p-values for multi-level categorical predictors, sequential
    Type I sums of squares, and plots whose summaries do not match the fitted
    linear model.
